page.title: 01THE AREA - General
page.content: The area is entirely rural .It has been found that most of it is covered with crops.There is an abundance of wild flowers to be found .There are four plantations of larch,cherry and evergreen trees. The highest part in the area is 105 metres above sea level.Only a few fields are to be found left for grazing land.There are to be found several disused chalk pits.The chalk was used to build the local houses in the distant past. There are several woods in the area, mostly made up of evergreen trees.It is to be found that larch trees grow in one of the plantations. Evergreen trees grow in all of the plantations. All the woods have deciduous trees mixed in with the evergreens.
